description: The Guardian’s picture editors select photographs from around the world
maintext:
Miami, US Sage Colina holds a dog called Rihanna as she is prepared to be adopted from the Humane Society of Greater Miami in Florida. The shelter is experiencing an overcrowding crisis, like many nationwide, with people releasing their family pets to animal shelters when they can no longer afford to take care of them
Photograph: Joe Raedle/Getty Images
